Let's think step by step. We begin by squaring both sides of the equation as usual: \begin{align*}
    (\sqrt{x+\sqrt{3x+6}}+\sqrt{x-\sqrt{3x+6}})^2&=36\\
    \Rightarrow\qquad x+\sqrt{3x+6}+2\sqrt{(x+\sqrt{3x+6})(x-\sqrt{3x+6})}+x-\sqrt{3x+6}&=36.
\end{align*}

To simplify this, note that $$(x+\sqrt{3x+6})(x-\sqrt{3x+6})=x^2-(\sqrt{3x+6})^2=x^2-3x-6.$$Hence, $$2\sqrt{(x+\sqrt{3x+6})(x-\sqrt{3x+6})}=2\sqrt{x^2-3x-6},$$so our equation becomes\begin{align*}
    x+\sqrt{3x+6}+2\sqrt{x^2-3x-6}+x-\sqrt{3x+6}&=36\\
    \Rightarrow\q
